        <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <h3>Is ChatGPT or Copilot better for writing emails and documents?</h3>
    <p>Copilot wins for in-Office document creation because it can read your existing files and understand your organization's context. ChatGPT wins for general writing that requires creative prose, diverse tones, or content for platforms outside Microsoft 365.</p>
    <h3>Can ChatGPT replace Microsoft Copilot for Office users?</h3>
    <p>No. ChatGPT has no native ability to read, edit, or create Office documents. For Microsoft 365 users, Copilot's integration into Word, Excel, and Outlook provides productivity benefits that ChatGPT cannot replicate.</p>
    <h3>Which is more affordable: ChatGPT Plus or Copilot Pro?</h3>
    <p>ChatGPT Plus costs $20/month and includes the full feature set. Copilot Pro costs $22/month with Office integration. For users who don't need Office AI, ChatGPT is cheaper and more versatile. For Office users, Copilot's productivity gains justify the slightly higher price.</p>
    <h3>Which AI assistant integrates better with development tools?</h3>
    <p>ChatGPT offers Code Interpreter for Python execution and integrates with many development tools. Copilot includes GitHub Copilot for inline code completion in VS Code and Visual Studio. For conversational coding and debugging, ChatGPT is better. For inline IDE suggestions, GitHub Copilot excels.</p>
